Makes a very good, dense chocolate cake in the American style (as opposed to European style). It is slightly more crumbly than I like, but perhaps my farmer's market eggs were smaller than they should have been. The cake was very good the day it was made, but I like it even better now that it has aged a bit. I didn't have enough pans or time to make two separate cakes, so I used one 10" springform pan with nearly 3" high sides. The batter filled it to the brim, so I placed a cookie sheet on a lower rack to catch spillover, but there was only about a tablespoon's worth. Baking took longer, ca. 1.5 or so hours, but it worked. After cooling, I sliced it in half to create the layers. The frosting is quick and easy to throw together, easy to spread, nice and shiny, and tastes great.

