Exceptional recipe - very moist, very rich, but not as dense as a brownie. I made this recipe for my 5-yo son, so i used only 1 cup of coffee to melt the chocolate for the batter. I made up for the missing 1/2 cup of liquid with extra buttermilk (now 2 cups). SUGAR: i reduced to 2 1/2 cups, and the cake came out perfect - still very sweet to my taste. (Next time, i'll try using just 2 cups, and probably adjust liquid down a bit to maintain proper consistency) BAKING TIME: i two used 9" forms, and should have used three. Mine were full to the rim, and overflowing, so they were thicker than intended and my baking time went up to 1 1/2 hours. Next time, i'll use the proper amount and bake just the recommended hour+. DONENESS: i took them out when the wooden stick came out barely clean - it was still getting slightly brown, but didn't pull gooey chunks of dough behind. Overall a fantastic cake - we got lots of compliments at the party. Thank you!

