Mousecrash, I admire your adventurous spirit! I have made this recipe into some tall cakes, but never even considered nine layers. And you want to double that! The only advice I can offer is to use a very large pan because the wider the base, the taller you can make the structure without it toppling. And then give some thought about what tools you would use to transfer the layers. And consider if servings of your finished cake will even fit on a plate! Or, make your 9-layer cake and give your sweetie two slices and remind him how lucky he is to have you as his girlfriend.

