Without a doubt the most delicious chocolate cake I've tried. The use of high-end chocolate is totally unnecessary and -- given how much chocolate this recipe uses -- too expensive. Ghirardelli is more than fine. When I was looking for a good chocolate cake recipe, I originally attempted one from Cooks Illustrated, my go-to source for all the basics. They claimed that "dairy muted the chocolate taste" but their resulting cake was VERY dry and disappointing. In contrast, this one is everything a chocolate cake should be: tender but sturdy, intensely chocolatey, and moist. Be aware that the frosting, like all ganaches, is quite dense.

