Rating: 4
I found this recipe to be an excellent one. I stumbled upon it, not knowing about it's famousness due to the today show. I don't bake often (more of a grill/saute/slow cooker kind of guy, as they are more forgiving), but I found this recipe to be very detailed and accurate. I did however make a minor variation that made it wonderfully chewy and kept it from getting too crumbly. I had done a big shop, and was operating under limited time. I suddenly found I had a lot less cocoa powder than I thought I had; I DID however have a can of chocolate syrup (Hershey's classic) in the fridge. So the end result was about 3/4 cup Chocolate Syrup, SUBTRACTING 1 cup cocoa powder, and 25% of the oil. This resulted in a luscious, chewy, tight texture that still maintained a surprising fluffiness to it. It enabled me to carve it easily into the two tiers. I was also a bit more financially constrained, so I found that Ghiradelli chocolate had to suffice.

