Rating: 4
I followed the recipe for the most part. It turned out very well. It is extremely easy to make and looks wonderful. For the people that think it was too dry or crumbly: try not baking it for so long. Test it every so often if you're worried about it getting dry. I am in Germany and I can't find corn syrup, or I don't know the translation, but I used High Tannin Honey instead which is a superb addition to the frosting. I used sunflower oil which isn't apparent either way. I only have 9" pans which worked out fine: i didn't fill them all the way, instead I made on the side three small chocolate torts which only took about 15 minutes to bake. The frosting was immediately a desirable consistency without cooling too much or refridgerating. I am from chicago, and to me this could almost be a Portillos Chocolate Cake substitute which I am very excited about. And anyone from Chicago knows what I'm talkin about. DA bears. I put raspberry preserves in between the two layers and the frosting on the top and sides and it is absolutely amazing. I highly recommend it!

