I know it's annoying when somebody reviews a recipe that they altered, but it's realistic-- sometimes you just have to make substitutions. I had to use some whole wheat flour in this recipe because I ran out of all- purpose, and I had to eyeball the amount of chocolate because my scale was broken. That may have contributed to the delicate texture, but a lot of comments have mentioned it as a problem. I think the best thing to do would be to freeze the cake before unmolding it. I personally baked it in muffin tins to avoid the heartache of trying to frost a cake that doesn't want to stay together. Other than that, it tasted amazing. I was worried that it would taste too much like coffee (the batter tasted more coffee-like than chocolaty), but after baking it just tasted like the most satisfying, dark chocolate cake. The glaze was a beautiful texture, but it really needed a teaspoon or so of vanilla to round out the flavors.

