Awesome. I made the recipe as cupcakes, using Green and Black organic baking chocolate for the batter (no need to chop - it melts if you breathe on it) and Sunspire semi-sweet chips for the ganache. The cupcakes took about 35 minutes at 325 degrees (not 20 minutes, as some other reviews state). I used parchment baking cups, which may have been the difference. I also made some mini cupcakes (1-inch, not 2.5) and those took 20. I let the ganache set up before frosting, but after the first few cupcakes I got lazy and remelted it. Then I poured about a tablespoon on each cupcake, let them sit for a few minutes. and then poured another tablespoon. Looks cool, tastes wonderful.

