Rating: 4
Wow. I adapted this recipe to make a three-tier wedding cake. One double recipe yielded three generously sized layers (one each of 14, 12 and 6 inches round). My only modification was to add one whole egg to each double recipe for more solidity- by no means did this compromise the moist, fudgy crumb of this cake. I made two double recipes and wrapped each layer in plastic wrap and heavy duty foil before I froze it in my deep freezer for a week. It froze beautifully. I skipped the ganache and filled and frosted the cake with vanilla flavoured swiss meringue buttercream. I studded the filling with fresh raspberries to offset the sweetness of the cake and the richness of the buttercream. Was it ever a hit! There's something to be said about 100 people applauding your handiwork. What's great about this cake is that you can really taste the chocolate; its texture and taste are a cross between soft, fluffy cake and moist,fudgy brownies.

