My high altitude go-to cake. I'm at 6500 ft. I add an extra egg, reduce the sugar by 1/2 cup, add 2 tbl more flour, and cook 20 degrees hotter. The higher temp helps set the cake + keep it from falling. In mid-winter when humidity is routinely 10% I'll probably add extra buttermilk to compensate for the drier flour.

