OK. I am on my 3rd try with this cake, and it keeps falling. I live at high altitude (8200 feet) and here are the adjustments I have made so far: Sugar reduced by 6 Tbsp; flour increased by 1 Tbsp; baking powder decreased by 1/2 tsp; buttermilk reduced by 3 Tbsp; eggs increased to 4; heat adjusted to 375F (300 seemed a little low to me even at sea level?), pans near 2/3 full. Rack in middle of oven. Friends want this as a wedding cake - love the flavour, if only I could get it to stop falling (although it falls less everytime I make an adjustment). Any suggestions? Thanks.

