Rating: 4
This cake with the frosting was fabulous. This would be great for any chocoholic. It is as good as the chocolate frosted chocolate cupcakes from Cheesecake Factory. To me, the chocolate ganache frosting was like eating a rich chocolate truffle. I made the following changes: 1) halved the recipe since I only wanted to use two 9'' round pans with no leftover 2) reduced the sugar by half a cup (and then scaled that amount down by a half since I wanted half the quantity overall 3) halved the frosting recipe since I did not want to use the frosting between layers. Even with this change, I had frosting leftover to dip my strawberries 4) I greased and floured the pan and also the parchment paper. Between layers, I spread a thin layer of seedless raspberry preserves. It complimented the cake very well. Even without the chocolate ganache between layers, the cake was incredibly rich. In the future, I might reduce the frosting quantity or skip the frosting altogether.

