Rating: 3
A word on the ganache frosting...I made it exactly to the recipe, but wanted something a bit lighter for the frosting. So after it had cooled to workable temperature, I beat it with a hand mixer for about five minutes. This lightened the color a bit, and also increased the volume slightly. I will definitely make this cake again. However, next time, I will flour the pans, increase the oven temperature to 325, and use 3 deep 9" layer pans, rather than regular-depth 9" layers. The layers fell slightly because the batter was just starting to go over the edge. It all tastes great though--like a big, fudgy truffle!

