So I made this cake about 2 years ago for the first time and loved it then, but the more I have made it, the better it has gotten. I use ghiradelli chocolate and cocoa and bake it in three 9" cake pans at 300 degrees for 48 minutes. I agree with everyone else that it is imperative to butter and flour BOTH the pans and then the parchment paper - otherwise the cake just won't come out of the pans. I use a chocolate buttercream in betwen the layers and then use the ganache for the outside. Even doing this, I just have enough ganache to cover the cake. I can't imagine stretching it to use it between the layers as well. This cake is beyond fabulous and I always get rave reviews when I make it for parties.

