to the reviewer below me.... Why mess up this perfectly fine recipe? You made a lot of changes to this cake. Just for fun I made both versions and brought them to a New years eve party. Guess what? The guests at the party preferred the actual recipe as listed. The only thing I would recommend doing differently is using parchment paper instead of wax paper, every thing else creates a different kind of cake. Also your frosting was not really a ganache. The recipe in calls enough chocolate for a ganache style frosting and this is why so many people LOVE this cake!

Rating: 4
BAKERS/COOKS!! Let me tell you something!! I've been baking for over 35 years & this is by far the best Chocolate Cake I've ever made & tasted!! I've been baking since I was 12 yrs old. If anyone is having problems making this cake, then you're doing something wrong!! I made this cake the 1st time out & I did so by reducing all the ingredients by 1/3 so that I wouldn't waste that much in case it didn't turn out right. I used 2 - 9 inch pans along with Hersheys Chocolate. Now I use GHIRARDELLI Semi-Sweet Chips & Unsweetened Cocoa Powder. I've tweeked the recipe just slightly a little to take this cake to another level. The adjustments that I've made is as follows: Use Parchment Paper instead of wax paper. Use 2 3/4 cups of Soft n Silk Cake Flour instead of All Purpose Flour. SIFT TWICE!! Use 4 eggs instead of 3. Brew 3 CUPS, (THAT'S RIGHTY, 3 CUPS) of water with 3 TBSP of Dunkin Donuts Coffee. The Xtra 1 1/2 cups of water in coffee will replace using actual Buttermilk. Instead use 7 TBSN of SACO CULTURED POWDERED BUTTERMILK BLEND. Sift this in with the flour. This powder is the bomb!! Regular Buttermilk can't touch this stuff!! Their Buttermilk pancake recipe is the bomb too. Not only that, it will save you money in the long run for using regular buttermilk. When stirring 4 eggs, add 1 TSPN of Vanilla along with Vegetable Oil & 3 cups of sugar. DO NOT SIFT SUGAR WITH FLOUR!! Mix for 4 mins with egg mixture. Add FLOUR/BUTTERMILK MIXTURE & COFFEE/CHOCOLATE MIXTURE alternately to eggs, sugar, oil, & vanilla. This batter can be used in 3 - 9 inch pans as well as 2 - 10 inch pans. USE A OVEN THERMOMETER!! Oven temperature could change according to what type of pans yu use. Pans should bake in 45 - 50 mins. FROSTING - Use just 8 oz. of chocolate instead of 16 oz. This will help make the frosting more creamier & not as thick. If you have any questions, you can e-mail me at MARYHEMBY@SBCGLOBAL.NET. Happy Baking

