Rating: 4
I have been making this recipe for about 3 years now- it's always a huge hit. I tinkered with 7 different chocolate cake recipes, trying to find "the one" for my husband. This is his idea of perfect chocolate cake and he won't let me make anything else for his birthday (he doesn't even want a cake from a bakery). I bake the cake using semisweet ghirardelli chocolate the night before so it has sufficient time to cool. I also tightly wrap it in the cake pan with aluminum foil right after it comes out of the oven so none of the moisture escapes- this works great and it stays SO moist! I make the ganache in the morning, also giving that plenty of time to cool before applying and then refrigerate the cake inside of a portable plastic cake holder. It's so good cold! Coffee is not supposed to be a distinctive flavor- often coffee is used in chocolate recipes to enhance the flavor of chocolate, not stand on its own. I personally use a chocolate flavored coffee because my husband can't stand coffee (he had no clue it was in the cake) and I didn't want to risk it! The more chocolate the flavor, the better anyway. This is definitely deep and luxurious.

