Rating: 3
I have a copy of this recipe from the LA Times S.O.S. 9/17/2003. It gives a double recipe for the ganache frosting. 2c. heavy cream, 1/4 c. sugar, 1/4 c. light corn syrup, 1 lb. bittersweet chocolate, chopped, 6 Tablespoons unsalted butter, cut into sm. pieces. (Same prep. instructions) Also that recipe calls for a 350 degree oven and an apprx. 45 min. baking time. Everything else about the recipe is the same.I used 3 9" pans so the baking time was 30 min. I agree it's a bit crumbly but a great flavor. A the double recipe for the frosting is plenty.

