Rating: 3
Overall, a great cake. But, given the rave reviews here and the time spent making it, I made sure to really taste both parts - cake and frosting - individually, and then together. I thought the cake was moist but crumbly (to preclude this, I'd slightly decreased my dry ingredients per the comments of a baker from Holland), and not as chocolatey as I'd have expected/liked. The frosting was so decadent (w/ Callebaut semisweet choc.) that a few of us felt ill afterwards, and it hardened to the point that it broke into pieces when the cake was cut. In the future, to the cake I'd add more chocolate (maybe 4 oz.), use stronger coffee, and cut the dry ingredients a tad more. To the frosting, I'd add a bit more cream, halve the corn syrup, and cut the sugar altogether. Nevertheless, everyone loved it, and called it "spectacular."

