I have made this cake with the cheapest chocolate I could get (Sam's Choice) up to medium expensive and I have come to the conclusion that this recipe is so good that it's going to produce an exceptional cake no matter what! It is my favorite of all the chocolate cakes, and I agree thoroughly with the reviewer's comments on "brown" cakes vs good chocolate cakes. My grater was dull, so I bought mini chocolate chips and they worked fine. If my chocolate isn't melted in my coffee, I microwave it a little to hasten the process and it works well for me. I also had only one ten inch cake pan and baked the layers one at a time and that worked well. I do agree that timing is important in baking this cake. I take mine out JUST WHEN the cake tester comes out clean(for my oven I start checking it at 45 minutes). I have also used salted margarine for the ganache and, for me, at least, it turned out fine too. I get rave reviews from this cake, even from my brother-in- law who isn't much of a sweet eater - he made my day by having two pieces! I like this so well, I got a bigger cake plate just for this cake. Thank you, to Epicurious, and whomever is responsible for this spectacular recipe.

