Rating: 3
The cake itself is phenomenal, perhaps the best chocolate cake I've ever had. It's dark, sweet but not too sweet, with excellent texture. You can't taste the coffee (it just adds to the dark chocolate flavor). The color is beautiful as well. Don't worry about "not Dutch process" cocoa -- I used Dutch process and it was fine. Drawbacks: it took an hour and 40 minutes to cook, and even then it might have done better with 5 extra minutes. This didn't bother me (what's more fun than being in a kitchen full of the smell of a baking chocolate cake?) but it might be an inconvenience to some people. Also: the frosting is so so. It's pretty much melted chocolate chips (I used Ghiradelli semi-sweet), with just enough butter to keep is smooth. It tastes good, but is a weak pairing to such an excellent cake. I suggest this cake, but another frosting.

