To a cook in Holland re: why can't you use dutch processed cocoa in this recipe: Don't take it personally !! It has something to do with the acid level in regular cocoa that reacts better with the baking soda. I suspect the Dutch processed cocoa would leave this cake a bit flat! This is a great cake and I make it lately with a marshmallow fluff instead of the ganache for a little contrast to the dense chocolatey-ness of it !! I think what you could use is the same stuff in epicurious.com's "de vil dog cake;" I use the recipe off the cover of Dorie Greenspan's "Baking. "

