I'm sold. I was skeptical that this cake could be as good as the hundreds of glowing reviews, but it is. I made it exactly according to the recipe, no variations. I used the video techniques to ice the cake, and it turned out even more lovely than the photo here - a glossy, smooth, flawless chocolate surface that I further decorated with little frosting roses from my pastry bag. I used two 9 inch pans and baked for just under an hour. I thought the cake layers were too soft and maybe I should have cooked it longer at first, but once the cake was together, my concerns vanished. It was dense, moist, not at all crumbly. The ganache is amazing and its consistency "holds" the cake together beautifully. There is absolutely no coffee taste in the cake, even though you can still taste the coffee if you lick the batter beaters! Because I used the smaller pans, I made cupcakes with the extra batter, and those were yummy too. I can't imagine really ever needing to try another chocolate cake recipe now.

