Rating: 0
Being a professional baker, I have my tested and proven recipes. Yet I could not resist to try this one after reading all your concern.Well..I must say: for an American recipe it is not bad. American recipes are usually high in flour,sugar and raising agents, and poor in eggs and butter. So is this one, but the European style ganache frosting supports it a great deal. Alltogether a nice cake; could be served with some raspberry coulis and whipped cream on the side. The cake is indeed moist, so complains from some of you about dryness comes forth probably from the following. As you use the cup system to measure your ingredients, every single person has his own way of filling the cup, being more or less precisely. Fill your cup with flour and cocoa a little higher, and you end up with a dry crumbly cake. So my advice: get away from the cup measuring and use the scale. Write down your recipes in grams or ounces amd everything will be much more precise.

