I made this in Dec for a couple birthdays and it's my favorite chocolate cake recipe! I used 1 9" round metal cake pan, and poured the rest of the batter in cupcake pans. I happened to use 1 metal cupcake pan and 1 silicone (that was what I had.) The cupcakes in the metal pan turned out perfectly round and nicely risen. For the cook from Berlin - the cupcakes baked in silicone didn't rise as nicely as those in the metal pan and came out really flat and the tops spread quite a bit. They also took longer to bake than those in the metal pan. Even though they looked bad, they tasted as good as the cupcakes from the metal pans. For the single layer cake, I topped it with a simple ganache, spread it around the top and sides and then let it set. It made a really easy delicious birthday cake with a smooth glossy top.

