Rating: 3
A very impressive and yummy cake! This IS a tricky recipe. Chopping a pound of chocolate is right up there with root canal so I used 2 bags of Ghirardelli chocolate chips  high quality and easy! This frosting recipe is quite a temperamental piece of work. Do NOT over mix and when you pour the mixture into a bowl, use one thats micro safe in case you need this step. Its supposed to thicken up sitting on the counter as it cools. This is good in theory but you would have to baby sit it and catch it at the right time! After a couple of hours on the counter it was still runny so it went in the fridge for a few hours. When I took it out it was hard. Decided to microwave it for 45 seconds at 50% power. It had a few little lumps quite as silky but acceptable. One second longer or a higher heat and it would have been too runny. Next time Id put it in the fridge immediately and then check on it every 30 minutes. The frosting recipe was just enough for the 3 layers but dont spread too generously between layers. You need every bit for the sides. For the cake I used Scharffen cocoa which was expensive but delicious. I put the batter (again do not over mix!) into 3 9 pans which filled the pans up half way (would not go more to avoid overflow). I did 45 minutes exactly but I would start checking at 40 minutes to get a moister product. I greased the pans with Crisco then put in parchment, greased again and coated with cocoa powder. The cakes did release easily but left a small layer of cake in the pan so I would dust more heavily. Is this recipe is worth so much angst? You decide!

