Rating: 4
I had to make this cake after reading nearly all of the reviews. I hadn't intended to read them, but with so many, I wanted to see what was going on. It was quite entertaining -- especially the debate about whether this recipe warrants this many reviews. Regardless, I made the cake for my son's 15th birthday to feed a large group of foodies. I used 9.5" square silicone baking pans. The recipe was followed exactly -- baking time and all, although I did use convection. I filled it with a mix of lightly sweetened cream and strawberries, then covered the cake with the frosting by pouring it slowly, and spreading it until it oozed over the sides. Everyone enjoyed this very chocolaty, rich cake. The cream and strawberries were a great accompaniment to the chocolate. The coffee taste mentioned by others was not noticed by any of us -- even those who do not like coffee. The texture of the cake is dense, but not as dense as that of a brownie. I used a combination of Scharffen Burger and Valrhona chocolate because that's what I had on hand. I won't get into the debate about whether this is THE chocolate cake I'll choose whenever we want chocolate cake because there are too many other recipes out there to try. Still, it is an exceptional cake that should be tried.

