This is a keeper!! Both the cake and the ganache were easy to make for something so impressive, and the ganache in particular blew my guests' minds. The combo of buttermilk and coffee for the batter liquids is a terrific idea, adds such depth of flavor without being too sweet or heavy. My rookie-to-this-recipe mistakes were overmixing the cake batter slightly, making it a tiny bit chewy (just follow directions better than I did - personally, next time I would alternate dry and wet in 3 or so additions, to get everything mixed in there faster without splashing stuff all over the counter by adding all the wet first) and trying to ice the moist room-temp cake layers with ganache that had been in the fridge (because I had to make the cake in stages).

