Rating: 4
I used 9-inch pans and just used about 80% of the batter. The cake and ganache both came together very easily. I had a similar idea to my fellow Minnesotan who used chocolate-dipped strawberries. I dipped Bing cherries in the ganache when it was very liquid and then used those to ring the outside of the top layer. I also cut up about a cup or more of cherries, added some cherry preserves and a tiny bit of kirschwasser. Then I put that in the middle layer over a some ganache. The only problem I had was that the ganache got a little stiff and was then hard to work with. It was very liquid, so I put it in the freezer and then the refrigerator. It took a while to set up but then it stiffened quite a bit. Next time I would watch that more carefully so I catch it before it gets to that point. Otherwise, no problems and everyone loved it.

