Rating: 4
I've made this lots of times--now that I live at 7000 feet I made some modifications and it turned out better than it did when I lived at sea level. Go figure. Used 18 ounces sugar 14.5 ounces flour, reduced both leavening agents by about 1/3, and increased the buttermilk by 3T. Love the look with 10" pans--invested in these after the first time I made the cake. If you have leftovers, they freeze well, and, even better, if you microwave a slice the ganache turns into hot fudge, just add a little mint-chip ice cream. YUM!!

Rating: 4
If you're looking for a down and dirty, fudgy, better than Mom's kind of American cake...you've found it. This cake is moist and uber chocolaty. I was searching for a perfect fudge cake to call my own (quite an undertaking for a perfectionist) and with a few modifications this could be it. Go ahead and try this cake before modifying it; you just might LOVE it as is. I personally think this cake is a little too moist (I know, can you believe it) so I have opted to substitute melted butter - slightly browned - for the oil and use 3 medium eggs as opposed to 3 x-large eggs. If this does the trick and gives the cake a little finer texture and a little less moisture as I imagine it will then I can stop the search. The chocolateyness is perfect. Mom thought it was a tad bitter, but being from Oregon means that strong coffee is synonymous with espresso; so weaken the coffee if you want a mellower bite and keep in mind Moms favorite chocolate cake is a pale brown. This cake holds well and maintains its texture even when served right from the fridge. The frosting is fabulous! I threw in an extra handful of bittersweet chocolate to ensure it set up properly...probably an ounce or so. All in all this is a great cake. And for those reviewers acting all snotty over the texture and going on about cake flour and crumb please understand this is a fudge cake this is not a sponge, a financier or genoise. Those are a different animal completely&this will not work as a tort base, a roll or with buttercream. This is a diner style, good ol Chocolate Cake straight up! Enjoy it.

