Rating: 4
This cake is so good I used it at the bakery where I worked for the past 11 months and I had trouble keeping it stocked because it was our most popular item. I find that the difficulty of preparatiion is in beating the eggs stiff enough. It will help to slightly warm the eggs before whipping, if they're cold, and you may need to whip longer than the recipe says; they should be pretty stiff! I don't use the filling or icing recipe that accompanines it. Serve at room temperature.

