If you're looking for super rich, indulgent, over-the-top good chocolate cake, this is it. I'm not sure if it was the way I made it or it was suppose to be as dense as it was, but it almost had a cheesecake quality to it. It is hard to describe. A used Dutched process but omitted the baking soda. I'm not sure if this created the super dense texture, but it was a great side effect. A few tips: I also used full-fat buttermilk. Considering the calories already in this cake, it didn't make sense to me to use non-fat. Also, check out your store's bulk section for Callebaut and Guittard semisweet chocolates. That's where I found it at my local grocery store. I put a full review on my blog: http://dozenflours.blogspot.com/2007/02/richards-double-chocolate-layer-cake.html

