Rating: 4
Lovely lovely cake. I did a few substitutions though. Instead of ganache in the middle, I made a hazelnut filling with nutella and frangelico and some chopped hazelnuts and dark choclate and a few more things. Just to cut down on the chocolateness of it. Its lovely either way though. I also covered the sides with chopped toasted hazelnuts, because I like the contrast of the crunchy hazelnuts and moist dense cake. For people having problems with ganache, the curdling and gritttines, that's a result if overmixing. for the curdling, just strain and add a bit more cream. Be very gentle when adding cream. For the grittiness, try to strain it to see if that works. Thanks so much, this was great.

