This is the second time I have made this cake and I've already broken my New Year's resolutions by scarfing leftovers! Two tips: make sure the coffee isn't super strong and use the full amount of sugar if you are using bittersweet chocolate. The first time I made this, I used superstrong french press coffee and cut the sugar. The batter was not very sweet, but thanks to other reviewers I made the chocolate caramel icing from somewhere else on the site and it was fine. This time, I made sure to use normal strength coffee plus didn't cut the sugar. I filled the cake with some vanilla buttercream (butter, conf. sugar, vanilla and whipping cream) then frosted it with a chocolate glaze and it was SUPERB. Many miles of bike-riding are now needed....

