i have been looking for the perfect chocolate cake base and i have found it! whoever made this cake and did not find it the most moist cake they have ever had... they did something wrong:). it is soooooo soft and moist. it's the perfect density... not too dense and not too light. i have made the triple choco celebration cake from this site a billion times and the components of the recipe are AMAZING. the cake base is like a fudge brownie and is absolutely delicious, but i have been looking for a lighter base that compliments the ganache, mousse and raspberry perserves. my search has ended. this recipe is it!!... and all of my new years guests(who have also eaten all my other cake-base variations of the triple choco celebration cake) agreed, too. things i did different: i used yogurt, because i did not have buttermilk on hand. i also used instant coffee instead of brewed. it took my cakes 1hr 15min to bake. i sliced the bases in half and filled bottom layer w/ rasp perserves, ganache and choco mousse... middle layer with rasp and ganache... and then rasp, ganache, mousse for the final layer. VERY decadent. regardless of what you pair with this cake base, it will compliment anything. obviously... i LOVED this cake:).

