Like many other reviewers, I have made this cake recipe several times - whenever I want a surefire hit that serves a ton of people. I usually use extra virgin olive oil - you can't tell and it turns out perfectly. Espresso isn't necessary - good old brewed coffee works great. For the ganache, I switch to a traditional ganache recipe with 1 1/2 cups heavy cream (brought just to a boil and taken off the heat) and stir in 12 oz good quality semisweet chips - it makes more than enough to coat the cake and it's much easier.

