Rating: 3
Really top notch chocolate cake. Some mods made it more worth the effort: I added cinnamon to the mix, which went very well with the coffee. Also, I modified the icing a bit; I used a 3 oz bar of Lindt (80% cocoa), a pint of cream, quarter tsp of salt (for richer, rounder taste), a half tsp cayenne, and deleted the granulated sugar. The icing is really a ganache with corn syrup to make it thick and sweet. I wanted a more "adult" cake with more complex but less sweet icing. Also, I've made this cake with Irish Cream-type liqueur subbing for the coffee, with the above ganache as an icing, which imparts a very rich and deep flavor. Covered with toasted coconut shavings makes it over the top, and my husband's long time favorite birthday cake.

Rating: 3
Yummy, but I've had a few issues. First of all, the baking time for this cake, is WAY over-estimated - I took my cake out at 53 minutes, and I think it was over-done. Number two, cake turned out very crumbly (maybe from over-baking?), and frosting turned out very dense (maybe from over-chilling?) and this made frosting it rather difficult, although the end result was still attractive. Also, serving it was difficult - they're not kidding when they say to leave it out of the fridge before serving. But I'm gonna give this cake another shot, and maybe it'll be 4 stars next time with a shorter baking time. Note - nobody has 2 10" pans.... I used 9" pans, and cut the recipe by a quarter; that was just the right amount of batter.

