Rating: 4
Outstanding! This is an excellent cake - very dense and moist. I used lowfat buttermilk, Hershey's Special Dark Cocoa, 60% cocoa "bittersweet" Ghirardelli baking chocolate in lieu of the semisweet chocoate and reduced the sugar from 3 cups to 2 1/2. Watch the baking time carefully. My layers were baked in just about 50 minutes - and I usually don't have to shorten baking times that much. I frosted with the chocolate buttercream frosting that can be found on this site under "devils food cake with chocolate-orange buttercream", Bon Appetit March 2004.

