Rating: 4
I am not a pro but this cake certainly makes me feel like one. It is my cake of choice whenever I need to make a chocolate cake. I've filled it with everything from raspberry jam, fresh strawberries, espresso with marscapone, and even caramel pecans and coconut for a killer german chocolate cake. I've even suceeded in making this cake at altitude. It cannot be beat and holds up well to a variety of fillings and frostings. I prefer buttercreams with this cake but just about anything works and it transports beautifully. Tip for slicing....use a very sharp - not serrated knife. Dip the knife in very hot water and then wipe the knife dry and slice. It is best to do this between each cut or at most two but you'll get a perfect slice - as thin or thick as you want. It sounds like a lot of work...but when presentation counts - this gets the job done.

