Rating: 4
I am very picky about chocolate cakes. Most of them don't taste like chocolate--they just taste brown, if you know what I mean. When I can't find a recipe I like, I tend to pick 5 promising ones, bake them all at the same time, and have a tasting party. This cake is heavenly, and won the taste test hands down. I've served it several times, and it's been a hit each time. I even bought the 10" pans necessary to make it, because the first time I made it in smaller pans and it just didn't come out right. I don't have any comments on the frosting, which I didn't use. My husband doesn't like ganache type frostings that harden after time, so I use a food processor recipe from the Joy of Cooking that stays soft and glossy for days. I can't remember the name of the recipe off the top of my head--but if you have the cookbook, you should be able to find it. The authors say that it's a particularly good frosting for children. Rave review aside, this is not a good cake for kids. The buttermilk and coffee give it a definite dark-chocolate adult cake taste.

