Rating: 4
I have made this cake too many times to count! I have some serious chocolate lovers in my family and this cake is perfect. My husband loves chocolate but not in such a rich dose, as this whole recipe is. I make the cake in 2 9" pans for about 50 minutes. I use parchment circles to line the pans that I've greased and floured. I have never had a problem with them sticking. I ususally make a mousse filling (from this site) and frost with buttercream to cut the richness. This cake is divine - moist and chocolatey. I would do the ganache if you plan on serving this cake to many people, as a small sliver would be perfectly sufficient OR if you are a die hard chocolate addict. Either way, this cake deserves at least 5 forks.

