Made the cake twice as listed. Next time, will try the seedless raspberry between layers as suggested. The chocolate frosting is a bit too much for me. Will read the reviews to find some way to lighten.

Rating: 4
MmmmMMmm. A perfect moist, fudgy, super chocolaty, old fashioned style cake. I chose to serve it frosted with a caramel ganache and it was divine. I have made this twice, the second time I cut out 1/2 cup of the cocoa powder and replaced it with 3T flour producing a less intense chocolate cake that is better suited for a chocolate fudge frosting...The original recipe is soo (deliciously) chocolaty that I almost prefer it with buttercream.Enjoy! PS: I have used both dutch processed (a more intense chocolate flavor) and natural cocoa powders and both work just fine.

