Rating: 0
Wow. This cake is outstanding - I would give it 5 forks if I could. It's incredibly moist, just the right texture and flavor -- perfect. I made it in two 8" pans and used the extra batter for cupcakes. Then I split the layers for a nice tall cake. Watch out if you decide to use this method, however, because this cake is so moist that it's more difficult to split than other cakes. I didn't give a rating since I only made the cake portion of this recipe -- I used the simpler ganache recipe found here: http://www.epicurious.com/recipes/recipe_views/views/105133 for the outside of the cake, and filled the layers with chocolate mousse from this recipe: http://www.epicurious.com/recipes/recipe_views/views/104512. It was to die for. To the cooks who claim there are "better recipes out there" -- if there are, please post a link!

Rating: 4
I've made this now three times. The first as cupcakes (see previous review) the second as a bundt cake - no frosting, just fresh whipped cream - and the third time i cut the recipe in half and made two six inch rounds. IMO, the ganache frosting for this is far too rich. The best alternative i've found so far is whipped cream and fresh berries. Definately a cake worth making from scratch.

Rating: 4
I just made this cake for the top layer of a wedding cake and for the groom's cake (in the shape of a glass of Guinness). The cake itself is great, although, I felt that it hit you almost too hard with the chocolatey flavour. I mean, I know that's what the cake is about, but it lacked a certain smoothness. Anyhow, it was still really great, and I loved the moist texture. I filled it with homemade raspberry preserves and used the ganache recipe. However, I needed extra frosting, so I made the ganache exactly as stated, and after chilling it and allowing it to ocme back to room temp, added 6 T. butter which had been whipped with 1 1/3 c. powdered sugar. This made it like a heavy buttercream and perfectly spreadable. To get a smooth-as-silk finish, I used a hot, wet knife on the outside of the groom's cake. I would highly reccommend this cake, both for the taste and the ease of making and working with it.

