I originally reviewed the cake in this recipe on 2/19/04 and this time made the cake with the ganache over the weekend. I again used 3 9" cake pans and baked ~45-50 minutes (keep checking for doneness with toothpick). The ganache was a tad tricky to me. I applied it in phases (between shoveling snow!). I refrigerated it for an hour as it was a bit thin initially and had to soften it on the defrost setting in the microwave for the final application. It was my husband's birthday cake and he thought it was quite good. (Personally, I still prefer a buttercream frosting.)

Rating: 4
made this as cupcakes - unbelieveable chocolate flavor. i used valhrona cocoa powder, which, imo, is the best. I thought the ganache icing was too rich, so i made the following changes: doubled the butter, used half and half instead of cream and used half milk/half semi-sweet chocolate. i cooled the ganache in the fridge, then whipped it until it was pale. the result was a rich, yet light "frosting" that melts in your mouth. (keep refrigerated). i also topped half of the cupcakes with the peanutbutter frosting from the brownie cupcake recipe also on this site - again, whipped the frosting to lighten it. utterly delicious.

