Rating: 4
Made this cake for a birthday party and all I can say is, "WOW!!". The cake was extremely moist and very rich. Baked the cake in three 9" cake pans using Valrhona cocoa powder and Lindt 85% cocoa bittersweet chocolate (which cut down on sweetness) and used Callebaut 65% cocoa semisweet chocolate in the ganache. The cakes came out perfect after baking for 40 minutes and brushed each layer generously with Kaluhua before assembling and added 1 1/2 tbsp. Kaluhua to the ganache. I also used a strong Italian blend coffee which added to the depth of flavour of the chocolate. Served it with homemade raspberry coulis and fresh whipped cream on the side. Can't wait to make it again!

