I made this cake for a birthday dinner and it turned out very well. Because I could only find super expensive cocoa powder, I did skimp a bit on the other chocolate, using semi-sweet Guittard chips sold in bulk at a local store. In a (sort of) unrelated incident, my sifter broke so I could not follow the sifting instructions. I was worried but in the future I would skip the sifting step. I also can't say I was 100% accurate with all the measurements (I don't have a scale so the 3 oz. of chocolate thing was guestimated). Even still, it was great to have a cake recipe that is a bit forgiving. It is also *huge*. I made for dinner for 8 and half was left over. Before frosting, I put the frosting in the fridge w/out even testing the consistency per the other reviewers and it was the perfect consistency. The only thing I would recommend is, when plating, set it atop some wax paper as the cake is so moist, it stuck to the plate I had set it on while doing other prep.

