I made this cake last week for my pregnant sis-in-law. She has called me every day since to thank me. My husband, who could do without chocolate most of the time insisted that this was the BEST cake he had ever tasted. The recipe was perfect. I had no problems- my 9 year old son helped too. Ganache went on flawlessly. My only suggestions would be DO NOT skimp and use cheap chocolate (I used Lindt, it's not the best, but better than Nestle or Hershey), allow frosted cake to sit in refrigerator at least 24 hours for optimum flavor and texture(it was even more moist after 48 hours!), and be sure to let it come almost to room temp before serving. I will surely make it again!

