Rating: 3
On the strength of the many superb reviews for this cake, I made this cake for Easter dessert...with a houseful of my daughter's college classmates as guests. I had previously hunted down and purchased the necessary 10" cake pans, and was eager to make what promised to be an exciting dessert. Yes, the cake WAS good, too, but it wasn't nearly as spectacular as I'd hoped it would be. Despite my ordinarily very efficient oven, it took nearly 1.5 hrs to bake the two layers, and even then I wasn't completely convinced that they were done. One stuck a tad to its paper liner, but not terribly enough to ruin the cake. However, both were a bit sunken in the middle, and I was worried about whether upending one layer onto the other would damage it while assembling and frosting the ensemble. As it happens, that worked out well...but there was only JUST enough frosting to fill and frost the cake. The frosting was excellent, however, and handled well. I might make this again and bake the cake a little longer still...or at a temperature higher than 300. (Did anyone else find this temperature peculiar?) I would also consider making 1.5 times the frosting recipe. I have a select stable of winning chocolate recipes that are better than this one, but this deserves a second chance...and it WAS still a delicious cake. Just not the "ne plus ultra" I had been led to expect.

