Rating: 4
A delicious, moist, easy, very chocolaty cake! My daughter requested chocolate cake for her 3rd birthday, and this cake fed 12 adults and 6 kids very well with leftovers! I folded a little whipped cream into a little of the ganache, to make a mousse filling for between the layers, which was a delicious contrast of texture. I spread/poured the ganache on the top thickly, and very thinly coated the sides, not worrying about appearance, as I planned on adding a layer of milk chocolate frosting on the sides, as well. When I chilled the cake, the ganache hardened, and I could spread the frosting on the sides and use some to write Happy Birthday on top. A few requisite sprinkles (very important when you are 3!) completed it. I will note that I had to adjust for altitude (we are at 5600'). I reduced the leavening by 1/4 and added some extra water to the batter. There was a slight dip in the center of the cake, easily filled with frosting, but I can't decide if I should do more or less leavening next time.

