I made this for a Superbowl party (chips and guac are SO passe). Fantastic, even when forced to use Nestle bars and resort to a few modifications: I only had 9-inch pans, which left me with enough batter to bake three layers. Only ended up stacking two, though, and kept the third for my greedy self (two 9-inch layers still made a tall, formidable cake, being so rich). Also, I added a little ground hazelnut to the middle layer of ganache for a subtle but tasty accent. Should have added more, it worked well. And I made some shavings from the chocolate bar to sprinkle on the top, which made the whole presentation quite professional. ("WHERE did you buy this cake?" they asked, setting aside their plates of guac. "Oh, I whipped it up this afternoon," I replied, ever so casually.) My advice on additions: A cake as rich and chocolatey and fanstatic as this stands alone. No reason to overly distract with raspberry jam, especially if you're using good chocolate. Other flavors would have been overkill.

