Rating: 4
First time I tried this I didn't adjust the leavening enough for the altitude here (about 3000 feet) and it rose very fast then sunk in the centre. But the taste and texture of this 'failure' was so good I tried again, reducing the soda to 1 and 1/2 tsp and the powder to 1/2 plus 1/8 tsp. Still sunk slightly, but almost perfect. Also used dutch processed cocoa because I don't like the red hue given by natural cocoa, and can only get crappy supermarket natural cocoa here or pay a fortune for organic stuff. Used Callebaut chocolate. Filled it with a not too sweet vanilla buttercream from Cook's Illustrated April 2000(so good!). This cake is what I think a chocolate cake should taste like and all tasters loved it. Can't imagine what the nay-sayers are expecting or doing to not like.

