and if you divide the cake ingredients by 2/3, don't scale back on the frosting. If you make a 9" cake, you still need a similiar amount of frosting as the 10" cake.

Rating: 3
You can cut the cake ingredients by 2/3 and use two 9"x1.5" round pans and it comes out to be a reasonable size (even then, we gave some of it away). The cake is very moist, but be sure to check on it every 5min starting from 40min because 9" pans will cook faster than 10" pans. Also, trim the sides if needed to make it even so the ganache covers the edges evenly. The frosting was awesome. One of the few frostings that leaves me feeling choco-bombed (though it overpowers the chocolatey flavor of the cake). It's even more chocolatey than Cheesecake Factory's 10 layer chocolate cake :-)

