Rating: 4
Loved it. Was skeptical about the hype but am now happy to add to the 4 fork parade. It was fudgy and rich, but has a light moist texture. The ganache is the perfect complement. It's also an easy & forgiving recipe: I goofed and baked at 350 (in 9x2" pans), checked at 50 minutes and found a dry toothpick, realized my error, shreeked and hoped for the best. It was the best, and now replaces my former standard choc. cake (Silver Palate Decadent Choc. Cake). I used the chocolate I had on hand: Ghirardelli semisweet bar from Trader Joes + Toll House chips - next time I'll upgrade to see if I can tell the difference. The cake fed 8 happy adults & 10 equally happy kids. Got Milk?

Rating: 4
I was skeptical about the hype but am now happy to add to the 4 fork parade. It was moist & fudgey, rich but not too, and the ganache is the perfect complement. Also, the recipe seems very forgiving! I goofed, baked at 350 (in 9x2" pans), luckily checked at 50 minutes and found a dry toothpick, realized that the recipe says 300, shreeked and hoped for the best. It was the best, and now replaces my previous choc. cake standard (Silver Palate's Decadent Choc. Cake). Instead of refrigerating the ganache, I spread a thin bit on the 1st cake layer, and stuck the layer in the freezer for about 10 minutes (per the Cranberry Choc. Torte recipe here). Then added a thicker coating, topped w/ the 2d layer, and frosted the top & sides. I used the chocolate I had on hand (ghirardelli semisweet bar from Trader Joes, and Toll House chips) -- next time I will upgrade to see if I can tell the difference. I thought the recipe yielded the perfect icing amount. It fed 8 happy adults & 10 equally happy kids. Got Milk?

