Rating: 4
I've probably made this recipe about 15 times since I "discovered" it almost 5 years ago, and it is absolutely THE best chocolate cake ever. It's moist, rich and dense without being too heavy or cloying. I have dreams about all the wonderful variations I could make with this recipe [seriously]. I use Van Houten cocoa and Lindt baking chocolate (not sure if you can get either in North America), and it turns out perfectly every time. I like the ganache, but I find that this cake PLUS ganache is really rich and to be served in small slices on very special occasions. I've made it with Vanilla Buttercream (Gourmet Entertains, January 2004), which is extremely labour intensive but worth the effort - it makes a beautiful cake and is a nice contrast to the chocolate. Re: leftover batter - I use deep 9" pans (instead of the 10" ones the recipe recommends), and usually have enough batter left to make a mini cake which I bake in the oven with the first layer (I have a small French oven...) and eat it while the second is baking! All in all, this is my favourite recipe for ANYTHING EVER!

