With regard to the comment on the rock hard ganache, I have had the same problem in the past. Different chocolate brands behave differently, but the more bittersweet, the harder it will turn out. I don't particularly like that. The best fluffy chocolate frosting I've had was a cream cheese frosting (you can't taste the cream cheese). Email me if you'd like a copy. Good luck!

