THIS CAKE IS FANTASTIC!!! This is my first review and this recepie made me write it!! I am a novice baker but even I could get a great result with this recepie. Folks who ate it eyeballs were rolling back, it was so good!!! The cake itself is moist, light and satisfying. It is not too sweet, nor is grainy. The ganache is out of this world. Put the two together and you have a MAJOR home run. The only small hitch was that I made the ganache the day before and put it in the fridge in a stainless steel bowl. Next day it was hard, so I reheated it over simmering water. No problem. But NOW it was too HOT!! So back in the freezer and checking and whisking until the consistency was right for spreading (not pouring). Took my freezer about an hour. Since the cake was for a special occasion, I used Scharffen Berger semisweet and cocoa powder. It was expensive but I've read that the quality of the chocolate does make a difference. Next time I would try other brands and see what happens. I would, without a moments hesitation, make this recepie again and again. The only changes I might make are to add a thin layer of rasberry jam for the filling layer, and serve some fresh ones with each slice.

