Rating: 2
After reviewing the 10 pages of glowing reviews, I decided to make this cake today for my sister in law. I followed the recipe exactly, with the exception of using Ghiradelli semi-sweet chocolate chips rather than bars. Big deal--the recipe says to buy semi-sweet chocolate and cut it into small chips. Also, I did use two 8 inch glass cake pans because I had no 9 inches. I remember thinking during the recipe that 1 and 1/2 cups cocoa was a lot, but I trusted the recipe. Bad idea. The batter was very rich and very chocolate tasting--better than a mix, of course. However, when the cake came out (check on it after 50 minutes rather than the 1and half hours recommended or it could burn quickly) I let it cool for more than an hour. The ganache icing I followed the exact recipe, and let cool while we went out to dinner. Came home, tried to assemble. The cake was so moist it wouldn't come out of the pan, finally breaking into three pieces. I used icing to "glue" the cake together and hide cracks. Now for the taste. TOO MUCH COCOA! The cake was moist, dense, rich, but almost bitter...the cocoa was too much, as was 1 and half cups coffee--you could taste bitter cocoa and coffee. The cake was too rich, and didn't even need icing. The icing was also "TOO" chocolatey and had no balance of flavors. The icing was, however, creamy and spreadable after more than an hour of cooling in the saucepot on the counter. Believe me, unless you like a very rich chocolate taste with nothing to balance the bitter cocoa flavor, DON'T MAKE THIS CAKE!

