This cake is excellent. I made one change and that was to use only half a cup of vegetable oil and a quarter cup of melted butter. Kept the cake moist but gave a hint of rich butter taste.

Rating: 4
I made this cake for my wife's birthday (she too is a chocoholic). This is, without a doubt, the best chocolate chocolate cake I've ever had, and certainly the best I've ever baked. I unfortunately didn't have access to more exotic chocolates, so I used Ghirardelli semi-sweet chocolate and Ghirardelli unsweetened cocoa power, but I don't know that it could have been much better (although I'd like to try different ones). The ganache retained a distinct hint of semi-sweetness, primarily because it doesn't have much else in it. But I think this is what makes it ... any more sugar, and the cake would have been too rich. Also, I agree with the other reviewer -- with the Ghirardelli chocolate, the ganache definitely had to be chilled. But it then spread very, very nicely. And the recipe was correct -- after cooling the layers, I needed to store them until the next day, and the plastic wrap worked well. The cake stayed moist after 24 hours like this at room temperature. Lastly, my recommendation to anyone who didn't like this recipe that much ... don't change the recipe! You'll be amazed at what a difference that simple recommendation makes. :)

