Rating: 4
YUM! I followed the recipe exactly, using 10" pans and my cake was done in 50 minutes. I was somewhat befuddled by the recipe's instruction to "cool layers completely in pans on racks... invert layers onto racks... and cool layers completely." I allowed my layers to cool in the pans for about 20 minutes before turning them out and they released easily. I tried the suggestion of one reviewer to partially freeze the cake layers before frosting. If anyone else takes this suggestion, please note that the cool temperature of the cake layers dramatically affected the spreadability of my frosting. You may not want to allow your frosting to thicken too much before attempting to spread it. Last, I found that I had more control over the frosting's consistency by chilling the frosting in a bowl in the refrigerator and stirring it about every five minutes rather than placing the bowl of frosting over a bowl of ice water which, even with constant stirring, seemed to thicken the frosting at the bottom of the bowl to a hardness that was difficult to reincorporate into the rest of the frosting.

