This is a really great cake and simple enough for beginners (like me). I have made this over and over, in a variety of pans, and have only had rave reviews -- it is now all of my family members' "birthday cake" (my youngest son is getting it this weekend)! One tip: this cake & frosting it is very easy to do if made in a bundt pan; once the cake has cooled I make 1/2 a recipe of the ganache frosting and just pour it over the top. It is also very pretty this way, especially garnished with fresh flowers or mint and berries. Please note, that when using a bundt pan, you will have excess batter (like when using 9 inch pans) but the cooking time is not much longer than when using multiple pans (approx. 15 - 20 minutes).

