Rating: 4
Hands down, the best chocolate cake recipe. Made this for the third time as well and received nothing but sincere compliments from friends. Many went back for a huge second helping. I find that using chopped chocolate works best (I used Ghiradelli semisweet). I've tried chocolate chips and found that it just does not turn out as well. Check the cake at 50 minutes---70 minutes is too long and the result will be a dry cake. It's a very moist and delicate cake, so frosting it may be difficult. I semi-froze my cakes (wrapped each in saran wrap), then frosted them. I only use 10 inch pans---end result is a fabulously huge cake. Great recipe!

