This is a wonderful, old fashioned, moist, coarse textured Devil's Food cake. I made it as a three-layer (9 inch)cake for a niece's 19th birthday. I used bittersweet (rather than semisweet) chocolate and put a layer of fresh raspberries between the layers, piled more on top of the iced cake, and decorated the plate with raspberries and fresh flowers. Rather than waiting for the icing to cool enough to spread, I put the cake on a cardboard round, placed it on a wire rack, and poured the icing over the cake. (I used two coats, and stuck the cake in the fridge to firm up between coats.) To insure I had enough icing, I made 1 and 1/2 times the recipe.

