For a quick cake with a similar flavor try this: 1 NON-pudding-in-the-mix chocolate fudge cake mix, 3 eggs, 1 1/3 c. buttermilk, 3 TB Cocoa powder, 1 tsp vanilla, 1/2 c. oil. Mix on low 1 minute, then on medium 2 minutes. Bake the same amount of time as cake mix directions. I've made this both ways, it's almost the same! For the freezing question - I decorated cakes for years and almost always froze the cake layers ahead of time. It also makes leveling and frosting a breeze!

Rating: 4
