Delicious chocolate cake. I made this cake in a 3-D cake mold and it turned out really well -- dense enough to stand up but incredibly moist. Also held up great -- baked on Friday but not served until Sunday (stored at room temp), and didn't dry out one bit. The coffee flavor was evident in the batter, but barely detectable in the finished product (and I used very strong coffee). Also I used bittersweet choc instead of semi-sweet, per an earlier reviewer, and I frosted with buttercream frosting instead of the ganache. I've made lots of different cakes for my 3-D molds and am often disappointed in the dryness (due in part to extra baking time usually required) but this cake was fantastic! Will definitely make it again!

