Rating: 4
After reading the rave reviews, I decided to make this cake as a Valentine's Day surprise for my chocolate-loving husband. I wanted to do right, so I bought two 10" round pans and followed the directions for the cake exactly. The flavors were great! (used Guittard chocolate chips from the local supermarket)... but the cake came out a little drier than I would have hoped. I baked the two rounds for exactly 60 minutes and I have a reliable oven thermometor, so I know it was right at 300 degrees. I would suggest checking for done-ness at around 45-50 minutes. Also, I put the ganache in the refridgerator for 2 hours then whipped it for more volume (no shine, but easier to spread). This cake is huge!! I look forward to taking it to a dinner party tomorrow (minus the two slices we had tonight) and testing the theory that the cake is better the next day. Great cake. Would make again... but watch that baking time!

