Rating: 4
I had fun reading everyone's solutions to the 10 inch cake pan dilemma. Here's my version. I have 9 inch pans, and not wanting the batter to overflow during cooking as I saw in other reviews, I used three 9 inch pans. Now I had three layers and wasn't sure there would be enough ganache. So, I whipped the leftover whipping cream from the pint I bought, and added it to 3/4 of the ganache making a chocolate whipped cream frosting for between the layers and put the pure ganache only on the top. It worked well, although, with three heavy layers, the cake wanted to shift. If I were to make it again, I would ice the first two layers, then refrigerate so it could set, then add the top layer and ganache and refrigerate again. Of course, you could also just make additional ganache and be true to the recipe. :-) Highly recommend this recipe though!

