Just a great recipe. I usually make one large single layer cake and several in 4 inch spring form pans. As my guests leave, I give them out. Sometimes, so I'm told, they make it all the way home. Also, I usually drizzle individual servings with a raspberry sauce, but the new favorite is a white chocolat (Lindt preferred)and cognac sauce. Melt the white chocolat in some very warm heavy cream to which about a jigger or two of good cognac has been added. A teaspoon of simple syrup or light corn syrup helps to keep it fluid. One friend would swap the cake for a cup of the white sauce. Keep up the good work.

