Rating: 4
This is just the best. Years of looking for the best chocolate cake; here it is. I've made maybe 30 or so; I sell them to friends or give for birthdays. My only addition to ingredients is to add the finely grated (then chopped) rind of two oranges. I make this a 3-layer cake by pouring 2/3 of batter in one pan, 1/3 in the other, and leave the heavier pan in oven a bit longer. Then, when it's cooled overnight (tastes so much better on day 2) and just slice the larger one to get my 3 layers. Then I spread a thin layer of seedless blackberry jam on the bottom 2 layers. My usual icing is whipped ganache, whipping it with extra cream, then masking the sides of cake with lightly toasted pecan or walnut bits, then pipe sweetened whipped cream flavored with a little Godiva chocolate liquer on top. Teeny dots of raspberry jam get piped w/paper cone onto the top of each whipped cream rosette. This cake gets so many compliments it's amazing. Fantastic recipe!!

