Rating: 3
A great, rich, dark, and dense chocolate cake. A couple of recommendations: 1) dont overcook it! I found 1 hour 10 minutes to be too much. 2) Use a good quality chocolate! The flavor and quality of the cocoa and chocolate used will definitley be obvious in the final result. 3) Slice a thin top off of the bottom layer to even it up and make it flat. I also sliced off the bottom 1/16 inch of the top layer to get rid of the slightly crusty bottom. 4) The cake is a little dense and mine came out a little dry. Some of the other reviewers have complained of dryness as well. Consider serving it with a raspberry sauce for addition moisture. 5) The rich chocolate ganache is perfect for a chocoholic. However, the cake can stand on its own with another, lighter icing or even with simple powered sugar if needed. 6) This cake is dense enough and big enough to serve 20 if needed.

Rating: 4
