Rating: 0
it does sound like you put in too much cocoa powder. 1 cup equals 8 fluid ounces, but not 8 dry ounces. since cocoa's a light powder, i would guess that 8 dry ounces of cocoa is much more than 1 cup. also, too much cocoa would result in exactly what you experienced -- dryness, and since cocoa doesn't have any sugar, too much tastes very bitter.

