Awesome! I made this cake for my friend's 23rd birthday (taking it along on our camping trip!) It was amazingly rich and sinful. The cake was moist and the frosting, when chilled, is reminicent of fudge. I cheated a little... the cake had to travel well, so I made it in a 11x14 sheet cake pan. I couldn't find Callebaut chocolate, but Nestle semisweet baking chocolate worked just fine. Even the "non-chocolate people" raved, braving the rain to stick around for some more. Give it a try... you'll be glad you did!

