Rating: 4
This cake was a big hit at a birthday dinner... I did make some changes to the overall recipe. Callebaut bittersweet chocolate was used in the cake. Rather than fill the cake with ganache (which I consider a coating) I used a milk chocolate mousse filling. The coolness of the milk chocolate mousse was an excellent foil to the rich dark chocolate. Halved the ganache recipe (used 8 oz. of Callebaut semi-sweet) and had plenty to cover the 10" cake. Another addition was candied orange peel for decoration. In future I plan to brush the bottom layer with a combination of Grand Mariner & fresh orange juice to add another dimension.

