Wonderful! Rich and decadent, but not too much so. Everyone raved, and for the record, a basic chocolate (I used Baker's) works well. I didn't have trouble with the cake crumbling -- used 2 9 inch pans and baked for about 55 minutes. Chilling the ganache gave it the perfect spreadability. Enough extra batter to make an thin extra layer for munching. Yum!

